Conditional Statement:
To make the set of instructions only when the given condition is true 
they are used to decide whether the code has to be executed or slip based on the given condition
executed line to line in sequence
•	Block of code: Set of instructions
•	Condition: An expression that evaluates an result(true or False)
•	Ex: conslole.log(5>6)
Methods
•	If else
•	Else if
•	Switch
•	Ternary operator
•	If
If: only one possible condition
If the condition is true it will execute otherwise skip 
Syntax:
If(condition){	

Ex1
let a=4
        let b=5
        if(a<b){
            document.write("hello skirt","<br>")
        }
        document.write("brilliant EI")

